<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Carlos says bla bla (Git)</title><link>http://carlosvin.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://carlosvin.github.io/en/categories/git.xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 25 Aug 2015 18:45:00 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>https://getnikola.com/</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Git proxy configuration</title><link>http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/git-proxy-config/</link><dc:creator>Carlos Martín Sánchez</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes working through a proxy is pretty tedious.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are going how to configure git to work through a proxy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A generic description, how to make git uses a specific proxy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;#http&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;git config --global http.proxy &amp;lt;protocol&amp;gt;://&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;password&amp;gt;@&amp;lt;ip_host&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-4"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;#https&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-5"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;git config --global https.proxy &amp;lt;protocol&amp;gt;://&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;password&amp;gt;@&amp;lt;ip_host&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-6"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-7"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;#to disable using proxy&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_d0c09ce637794cf3868bb7e6386fcb06-8"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;git config --global --unset http.proxy
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;dl class="docutils"&gt;&lt;dt&gt;protocol&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;Use to be http or https&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt&gt;username&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;The proxy user name&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt&gt;ip_host&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;Proxy host address&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt&gt;port&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;Proxy listening port&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt&gt;password&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;Your proxy password&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;/dl&gt;&lt;p&gt;More info in &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://git-scm.com/docs/git-config"&gt;official Git configuration&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>Git</category><category>Proxy</category><category>Tips and Tricks</category><guid>http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/git-proxy-config/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 15 Nov 2012 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>